cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of synthesizing future frames from a single input image, which is a common task in computer vision. The proposed approach involves a probabilistic model and a novel network structure, which are both relevant to the computer vision subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a probabilistic model also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves motion understanding, which is relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
